### Running Tests

<PLACEHOLDER: IF_PYTHON>
#### Python Testing (pytest)
- Run all tests: `pytest`
- Run tests with coverage: `pytest --cov`
- Run specific test file: `pytest tests/test_file.py`
- Run specific test: `pytest tests/test_file.py::test_function`
- Run tests in verbose mode: `pytest -v`
- Run tests with output: `pytest -s`
- Run tests matching pattern: `pytest -k "pattern"`
- Run tests in parallel: `pytest -n auto` (requires pytest-xdist)

#### Python Testing (unittest)
- Run all tests: `python -m unittest discover`
- Run specific test file: `python -m unittest tests.test_file`
- Run specific test: `python -m unittest tests.test_file.TestClass.test_method`
- Run with verbose output: `python -m unittest -v`

<PLACEHOLDER: IF_JAVASCRIPT>
#### JavaScript/TypeScript Testing (Jest)
- Run all tests: `npm test` or `jest`
- Run tests in watch mode: `npm test -- --watch`
- Run tests with coverage: `npm test -- --coverage`
- Run specific test file: `npm test -- test-file.test.js`
- Run tests matching pattern: `npm test -- -t "pattern"`
- Run tests in verbose mode: `npm test -- --verbose`

#### JavaScript/TypeScript Testing (Vitest)
- Run all tests: `npm test` or `vitest`
- Run tests in watch mode: `vitest --watch`
- Run tests with coverage: `vitest --coverage`
- Run specific test file: `vitest test-file.test.js`
- Run tests in UI mode: `vitest --ui`

#### JavaScript/TypeScript Testing (Mocha)
- Run all tests: `npm test` or `mocha`
- Run tests in watch mode: `mocha --watch`
- Run specific test file: `mocha test-file.test.js`
- Run tests with reporter: `mocha --reporter spec`

<PLACEHOLDER: IF_GO>
#### Go Testing
- Run all tests: `go test ./...`
- Run tests in current package: `go test`
- Run tests with verbose output: `go test -v`
- Run tests with coverage: `go test -cover`
- Run specific test: `go test -run TestFunctionName`
- Run tests in parallel: `go test -parallel 4`
- Generate coverage report: `go test -coverprofile=coverage.out && go tool cover -html=coverage.out`

<PLACEHOLDER: IF_RUST>
#### Rust Testing
- Run all tests: `cargo test`
- Run tests in verbose mode: `cargo test -- --nocapture`
- Run specific test: `cargo test test_function_name`
- Run tests with output: `cargo test -- --show-output`
- Run tests in parallel: `cargo test -- --test-threads=4`
- Run doc tests: `cargo test --doc`

